 {"id":"franken_networkx-qj6","title":"Extract min-cut comparison epsilon to named constant","description":"## What\n\nReplace 2 inline 1e-12 values in the minimum_cut/stoer_wagner comparison logic\n(fnx-algorithms line ~3197, ~3200) with the existing DISTANCE_COMPARISON_EPSILON constant.\n\n## Status: COMPLETED (March 2026)\n\nBoth occurrences replaced:\n- Line ~3197: cut.value + DISTANCE_COMPARISON_EPSILON < current_cut.value\n  (determines if a new cut is strictly better than the current best)\n- Line ~3200: (cut.value - current_cut.value).abs() <= DISTANCE_COMPARISON_EPSILON\n  (tie-breaking when cuts have equal value — uses deterministic node ordering)\n\n## Why DISTANCE_COMPARISON_EPSILON\n\nThe min-cut algorithm compares floating-point cut values. The epsilon prevents\nfalse \"better cut\" declarations due to floating-point rounding. Using the same\nconstant as other distance comparisons ensures consistent behavior across the\nshortest-path / min-cut algorithm family.\n\n## Files Changed\n\n- crates/fnx-algorithms/src/lib.rs (lines ~3197, ~3200)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-25T03:04:14.781406540Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-25T03:04:21.672208928Z","closed_at":"2026-03-25T03:04:21.671400738Z","close_reason":"Both inline 1e-12 values replaced with DISTANCE_COMPARISON_EPSILON. Verified.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
